          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "6-C-13",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.99
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Self-supporting 13C target of 45 mu-",
                "g/cm2 nominal thickness."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " An array of four double sided silicon strip",
                "detectors was employed in order to detect the four",
                "alpha particles. Each DSSDwas 500 mu-m thick and 5 x 5",
                "cm2 in active area. Each face was segmented into 16",
                "strips of 3 mm width, with the front face strips being",
                "horizontal and those on the rear face vertical. The",
                "detector distances and center angles were 10.0 cm and",
                "+50.8deg, 14.0 cm and +23.5deg, 13.9 cm and -28.6deg,",
                "and 10.7 cm and -54.5deg."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Events in which four charged particles were",
                "detected in the DSSD array were selected. Energy and",
                "position calibrations were applied to the data."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Authors used events with three incident alpha beam",
                "energies (27.0, 27.5, 28.0 MeV)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "As no particle identification was provided directly by",
                "the detectors, the four hits were assumed to be alpha",
                "particles in the analysis. The undetected neutron",
                "energy was determined for each event from the missing",
                "momentum between the beam and four detected alpha",
                "particles,"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
